rComments: Joel is an amazing professor! Aside from being super nice, he gives lots of opportunity throughout the semester to help you improve your writing skills. His lectures are very engaging, so participating is crucial otherwise you may miss important information that can be useful for your assignments throughout the semester. He is also a fair grader.
Funny guy, his fascination with the material is contagious. Seeing that he was a prof this year at UTSC rather than a TA is what convinced me to take my second Shakespeare course.

Joel was super helpful! He turned an incredibly complex piece of literature, and made it understandable, yet incredibly interesting at the same time. Super helpful to anyone who asks, you can tell he cares about his students. Love him!
